<h2>iOS</h2>
<h3>Flat Habits</h3>
<p>Inspired by <a href="https://jamesclear.com/atomic-habits">Atomic Habits</a>, I wrote <a href="https://flathabits.com">Flat Habits</a> for iOS.</p>
<p>Flat Habits is entirely offline and private. No ads. No cloud. No sign-in. No social. No analytics. No distraction.</p>
<center>
  <img alt='Flat Habits screenshot' width="350" src='https://is1-ssl.mzstatic.com/image/thumb/Purple125/v4/1b/fb/0f/1bfb0f89-8e2b-716b-a59d-dc1a9e6eca63/91fe385b-31ea-4d6c-afcf-38cde0a368a0_6l1.png/460x0w.webp'>
  <br>
  <br>
  <a href="https://apps.apple.com/app/id1558358855"> <img width="180px" src="https://plainorg.github.io/download-on-app-store.png" alt="Download Flat Habits from the iOS App Store"/></a>
</center>
<h3>Plain Org</h3>
<p>I'm an <a href="https://orgmode.org/">Org mode</a> fan, so I wrote <a href="https://plainorg.com">Plain Org</a> to view and edit org files from iOS. Also on the <a href="https://apps.apple.com/app/id1578965002">App Store</a>.</p>
<h2>*scratch*</h2>
<p>I wanted an Emacs-inspired *scratch* buffer on iOS (who doesn't?), so I built <a href="https://xenodium.com/scratch-a-minimal-scratch-area/">*scratch*</a>.</p>
